commit.message:
Allow primitive-0.9; add Haskell CI for GHC 7.10 - 9.8

Includes the bound changes made to `primitive` in revisions 1 and 2.
Tests only build with GHC 8.0 and up; reflected this in the `base` lower bound.

Removed old Travis CI.

Bump primitive upper bound.

Breaking change only impacts PrimArray, unused here.
Version 0.9.0.1

Allow building with vector-0.13.*

Adapted from the patch in erikd/vector-algorithms#39, with some minor tweaks:

* Since the `HasCallStack` constraint isn't available on all versions of GHC
  that `vector-algorithms` supports, I decided to omit the additional
  `HasCallStack` constraints that erikd/vector-algorithms#39 adds.
* I used `stToPrim` to accommodate the generic `Vector` classes specializing
  all of the monads to `ST` instead of being polymorphic over `MonadPrim m`.
* I also fixed the benchmark suite.
Version 0.9.0.0
Fix typos in comments

Add nub related functions

This adds a few nub related functions included a top-level
immutable variant based on Intro sort and a higher-order
version allowing choice of algorithm.

Add sortUniq function

Add a `sortUniq` function to each sort variant which
first sorts the vector and then does a pass to remove
all duplicates.
Relax bounds for vector-0.13
Correct a typo in LICENSE
Version 0.8.0.4

Intro.partialSort: Fix out-of-range accesses

Previously `Data.Vector.Algorithms.Intro.partialSort k v` would
stumble upon undefined behavior via out-of-range array accesses
if `length v < k`. Avoid this by clamping k to the length of the
region being sorted.
Fix upper bounds for QuickCheck
Add ghc-8.10 to travis setup and add cabal.project
Version 0.8.0.3
Fix out-of-bounds errors in Timsort
Enable vector:unsafechecks flag
Version 0.8.0.2

Fix bug in Data.Vector.Algorithms.Heaps.heapInsert

The previous code confused the index in the original vector and the index
shifted by the offset (the `l` in the code), and it would lead to an
infinite loop if the offset is non-zero. In order to fix this issue,
this commit makes sure that all the index variable in the loop is shifted.

cabal: Version 0.8.0.1

Closes: https://github.com/erikd/vector-algorithms/issues/12
test: Hide QuickCheck Sorted identifier
cabal: Bump upper version on QuickCheck

Halved memory usage of merge sort

The documentation at the top of `Merge.hs` claims "The temporary buffer
is preallocated to 1/2 the size of the input array", and this is now
correct.

We also save a few comparisons in order to be able to use one to avoid
allocating a vector if it won't be used at all.

Ceiling (`(len + 1)/2`) is used instead of floor (`len/2`) in order to
be able to fit the larger half of odd-length vectors.

Reduced memory usage of `simple-bench`

Even though the vector lengths used in each test are identical,
`simple-bench` allocates a new vector for every test it runs rather than
reinitializing the same vector repeatedly.

This can cause system freezes if the extra vectors overfill RAM and
start causing aggressive swapping.
